The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Essar Steel plans to hike capacity 

 OUR BUREAUX

 Jan. 28: Essar Steel has finalised plans to increase its capacity at its Hazira-based steel plant from 2.4 MTPA to 3.6 MTPA by March 2006.

 The steel company, which also announced its third quarter results today, said its income has gone up by 53 per cent in the quarter ended December 31 at Rs 1428.95 crore (net of excise). Net profit stood at Rs 197.54 crore compared with a loss of Rs.21.74 crore in the same quarter last year, after providing for finance costs of Rs.129.16 crore, depreciation of Rs.100.73 crore and provision for deferred tax of 5.49 crore.

 Besides higher prices of most steel products, Essar managed to improve its performance by increasing output. Essars steel production during the period was 5.41 lakh tonnes compared with 5.12 lakh tonnes during the same period in the previous year. 

 Total sales for the quarter stood at 5.24 lakh tonnes (5.02 lakh tonnes). The company reported domestic sales of 3.60 lakh tonnes (3.56 lakh tonnes and export sales of 1.64 lakh tonnes (1.46 lakh tonnes).

 The Essar share opened on the Bombay Stock Exchange at Rs 34.70 and closed at Rs 37.55.

 PNB net up

 Punjab National Bank has reported a 21 per cent increase in net profit at Rs 314.27 crore for the quarter ended December 31 compared with Rs 259.8 crore in the corresponding period last fiscal. 

 The total income increased marginally to Rs 2380.08 crore against Rs 2362.33 crore in the year-ago period.

 The bank also announced an interim dividend of 30 per cent or Rs 3 per share for 2004-05. 

 The record date for determining the entitlement of shareholders and beneficiaries to receive the interim dividend has been fixed as February 28.

 GSFC report card

 Gujarat State Fertilisers amp; Chemicals (GSFC) today reported a net profit of Rs 41.47 crore for the third quarter ended December 31 against Rs 80 lakh in the same period last fiscal.

 The total income during the reporting quarter rose to Rs 820.15 crore as against Rs 599.09 crore in the corresponding period of 2003-04, the company said in a release. 




